<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4914941>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 4. Shell and anatomy of Aliculastrum cylindricum. A. Detail of anterior part of shell. B. Detail of posterior part of shell. C. Detail of jaw. D. Front view of middle part of radula. E. Detail of median tooth and inner lateral teeth. F. Detail of outer lateral teeth at left side of radula. G. Top view of gizzard plate. H. Rods on middle ridges of gizzard plate. I. Male reproductive system. go, genital opening; pr, prostate; ps, penial sheath; sd, seminal duct. Scale bars: A, B, I = 1 mm; C = 2 µm; D = 100 µm; E, F, H = 20 µm; G = 200 µm. A–H: MNHN, Paris (S3/ OT236), H = 22 mm; I: MNHN, Paris, H = 13.7 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4914941/files/figure.png" .

